      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Non-Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  patients with moderate to severe RA.

          -  Inadequate response on earlier optimal use of a minimum of two DMARDs (disease
             modifying anti-rheumatic drugs such as goldsalts, salazopyrine, leflunomide,
             methotrexate (MTX)) as far as one of the two used DMARDs is MTX that at the exception
             of a documented intolerance despite the association with folic acid, should have been
             administered IM or oral during a minimum of 3 months and at a minimal dose of
             15mg/week.

          -  DAS 28 score ≥ 5.1

          -  For whom a drug that is registered for the treatment of moderate to severe RA is
             commercially available but does not constitute a satisfactory treatment for this
             patient.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
